commitResults.messageTitle: Add Save and Load function to BudgetBuddy
commitResults.messageBody:
The Chatbot is unable to retain any information between sessions.

Persistent storage for financial data (expenses, incomes, and budgets)
needs to be implemented to maintain data between app sessions.

Implement save() and load() methods in the Storage class to write to
and read from a file. Integrate these methods in the main program to
automatically save after each command and load data upon startup.

This approach ensures data persistence while keeping the logic
encapsulated within the Storage class.

Error handling is added to display a message if there is an issue with
file updates during save/load operations.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add Parser class to Implement command parsing logic
commitResults.messageBody:
This structure allows the application to process user commands
effectively and respond with appropriate actions or errors.

By delegating command handling to specific command classes and
validators, the design adheres to the Single Responsibility Principle,
enhancing maintainability and scalability.

commitResults.messageBody:
The Ui class will retrieve commands, display messages, and acknowledge

 principles.
